Using bash run 'sh configure.sh' which will execute an automatic configuration scripts.
The intention for this is to reduce time and effort on initial server hardening setup.
The script interacts by using case select.
Notice SWS root authority (sws.rootca.pem) is supplied.

For the ./Debian_packages folder include GPG keys with signatures or SHA-2 checksums.
    List:
          OpenSSH server
          Snort
          Apache2
          NextCloud server          

***Remember to ensure all programs, including the OS pass checksum validation.***


See the SHA-256 checksums for 'configFiles/'

